Probabilistic Methods. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the use of Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) methods, which are a type of probabilistic method used in Bayesian modeling. The panel of experts discusses various issues related to the use of MCMC, such as building confidence in simulation results, assessing standard errors, and identifying models for which good MCMC algorithms exist. The paper does not discuss any of the other sub-categories of AI listed.
